User Instructions

These are the menu options: 
1. (A)dd a Book
2. (R)emove a Book
3. (U)pdate a Book
4. (F)ind a Book
5. (S)ave your BookShelf
6. (V)iew your BookShelf
7. E(X)port to CSV and Excel
(Q)uit

Alwasy press ENTER after each input.
----------------------
How to Add a book:

To add a book, choose 1 or A.

The below prompt shows what users need to know to add a book. They will pop up individually after being filled out or pressing ENTER. 
        
        Title: Enter book title        
        Author: Enter author name
        Genre: Enter genre of the book(Fantasy, Fiction, NonFic, etc.)
        Year: Enter published year
        Form: Enter format of the book(Audiobook, Physical, eBook, etc.)
        Status: Enter state of completion(Completed, TBR, etc.) 
        Rating: Rate book on a scale of 1 to 5(1 = Bad, 5 = Awesome)
        Notes: Comments or reminders about the book  

You must have the book title filled out at minimum in order to save your BookShelf.
Once everything is filled out, press ENTER. This will make the main menu options appear again.           
----------------------
How to Remove a Book:
            
To remove a book, choose 2 or R.
            
The prompt below will appear: 
    
    Enter the title of the book you would like to remove: 

After entering the title of the book, press ENTER, and the below prompt will appear afterwards: 

    Successfully removed 'book title' from your BookShelf.

The main menu options will appear again at the end.
----------------------      
How to Update a Book

To Update a Book, choose 3 or U.

Enter the title of a book you would like to update. 

Enter updates in the needed fields. 
    This is how it will pop up:
    
        New Author(current: ): Enter new author name
        New Genre(current: ): Enter new genre of the book(Fantasy, Fiction, NonFic, etc.)
        New Year(current: ): Enter new published year
        New Form(current: ): Enter new format of the book(Audiobook, Physical, eBook, etc.) 
        New Status(current: ): Enter new state of completion(Completed, TBR, etc.) 
        New Rating(current: ): New book rating on a scale of 1 to 5(1 = Bad, 5 = Awesome)
        New Notes(current: ): New comments or reminders about the book

If certain fields don't need to be changed, simply press ENTER and the information will remain unchanged unless an entry is typed.
Once everything is filled out, press ENTER. This will make the main menu options appear again.     
----------------------
How to Find a Book: 

To Find a Book in your BookShelf, choose 4 or F.
Enter the title of the book you would like to find. 

If the book is NOT in your BookShelf, it will show: 
        Book titled 'Book Title' not found.

If the book is in your BookShelf, it will show the book information as: 

Book Found
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Title | Author | Genre | Year | Form | Status | Rating | Notes | 
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Example 1 | asdf | ghjk | 0000 | qwerty | zxcv |  |  | 
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The main menu options will appear again at the end.
----------------------
How to Save your BookShelf:
To save your BookShelf to the most recent, choose 5 or S.
This will pop up the prompt: 

        Bookshelf successfully saved to 'books.json'

The main menu options will appear again at the end.
----------------------
How to View your BookShelf: 

To View your BookShelf, choose 6 or V.

It will show all your books in this format:
        Here is your current Bookshelf:
        ----------------------------------------
        Title | Author | Genre | Year | Form | Status | Rating | Notes | 
        ----------------------------------------
        Example1 | asdf | asdf | 1234 | physical | asdf | 2 | asdf | 
        ----------------------------------------
        Example2 | qwer | qwer | 1234 | ebook | tbr | 3 | na | 
        ----------------------------------------
        Example3 | zxcv | zxcv | 1234 | ebook | tbr | 3 | a | 
        ----------------------------------------
        End of bookshelf.

The main menu options will appear again at the end.
----------------------
How to Export your BookShelf:

Users can export their BookShelf to a CSV file and view it in Excel by choosing 7 or X.
This will pop up the prompt: 
        Exporting your Bookshelf...
        BookShelf successfully exported to 'bookshelf.csv'.

Find the CSV file in file management, search for bookshelf.csv
In the CSV file, you will find the information about your book, including the Title, Author, Genre, Year, Form, Status, Rating, and Notes.
----------------------
How to Quit the Program:

To quit the program, press Q in the main menu options.
This will give you the option to save your BookShelf before you quit, choosing Y(Yes) or N(No).
Once you choose a selection, you will exit the program.
----------

The End of User Instructions
